<item>
            <title>[FLINK-5467] Stateless chained tasks set legacy operator state</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5467</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I discovered this while trying to rescale a job with a Kafka source with a chained stateless operator.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking into it, it turns out that this fails, because the checkpointed state contains legacy operator state for the chained operator although it is state less.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aljoscha&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aljoscha&quot;&gt;aljoscha&lt;/a&gt; You mentioned that this might be a possible duplicate?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
